# Cursor Rules CLI

A command-line tool for adding AI-powered documentation templates to projects using the Cursor IDE. These templates enhance AI functionality by providing structured guidelines that help the AI better understand and navigate your codebase.

## Purpose

Cursor Rules CLI simplifies the process of adding AI documentation to your projects. It provides a set of default templates that establish patterns and conventions, making it easier for Cursor's AI to assist with development tasks effectively.

## Key Features

- **Template Initialization**: Quickly add AI documentation templates to any project
- **Default Templates**: Includes ready-to-use templates for common documentation needs
- **Custom Rules Support**: Allows creation of project-specific AI guidelines
- **Simple CLI Interface**: Easy-to-use command line tool built with Bun

