├── example/                   # Example project for demonstration
├── src/                       # Source code for the CLI tool
│   ├── cli/                        # CLI implementation
│   │   └── actions/                     # Command handlers (init, version)
│   ├── core/                       # Core functionality 
│   │   └── file/                        # File system operations
│   ├── shared/                     # Shared utilities and constants
│   ├── templates/                  # Template files used by the CLI
│   │   ├── repomix-instructions/        # Instructions for code analyzer
│   │   └── rules-default/               # Default rule templates
│   └── wip/                        # Work in progress features
│       └── rules/                       # Draft rule templates in development
```

## Default Templates

The CLI provides the following default templates:
- **cursor-rules.md**: Guidelines for adding and organizing AI rules
- **project-overview.md**: Template for project description and purpose
- **project-structure.md**: Documentation of project structure and organization
- **task-list.md**: Guidelines for tracking project progress with task lists

## Usage

Install the CLI:
```bash
npm install -g cursor-rules-cli
```

Initialize rules in your project:
```bash
cursor-rules init
```

## Technical Implementation

The project is built with:
- **Bun**: As the JavaScript runtime environment
- **TypeScript**: For type-safe code
- **Commander.js**: For CLI argument parsing
- **Clack**: For interactive CLI prompts
- **Zod**: For configuration validation
- **Repomix**: For codebase analysis (optional integration)

